The paper discusses a general-purpose framework for employing Minimax distances with many machine learning methods that perform on numerical data. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of Minimax distances to extract features that capture underlying patterns and structures in the data, which could also place it in the sub-categories of cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
